    "# Iteration 4 — Integration of auto-select into the image module\n",
    "\n",
    "**Goal.**  Move the iter-3 candidate-bank scoring + selection out of the exploratory compute scripts and into the shared estimator module so application code can produce an image-only pia surface with one call.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Changes.**\n",
    "- Added two public functions to `code/dev_code/03_image_based_surface.py`:\n",
    "    - `score_surface_quality(surface, vol, z_um, xy_um, ...) -> dict`\n",
    "    - `auto_select_surface(candidates, ref_vol, z_um, xy_um, ...) -> (name, result, scores_df)`\n",
    "- Added a convenience wrapper to `code/dev_code/benchmark_analysis.py`:\n",
    "    - `estimate_pia_surface_image_autoselect(s, *, level=4, qcon_n_threshold=0.9) -> (surface, info, scores)`\n",
    "\n",
    "**Validation.**  Re-ran the 7-candidate bank on all 6 HCR subjects via the new API (`iter04_compute.py`) — the selected candidate matches what an independent `argmax Q s.t. Qcon_n ≥ 0.9` on iter-3 scores gives.  Result: every selection produces onset = 2.5 µm and above-fraction ≤ 1.13 %."
   ]
